  "prompt": "What programming languages are used at Quora ?",
  "response": "Quora primarily uses Python for its backend development. Python is a popular choice in the tech industry due to its readability, extensive libraries, and versatility. Here are some of the key programming languages and technologies that are used or have been used at Quora:\n\n- **Python**: The main language for backend development. Quora uses Python for server-side logic, API development, and data processing.\n\n- **JavaScript**: Used for frontend development to create dynamic and interactive user interfaces. Quora likely uses modern JavaScript frameworks or libraries like React.js for building the frontend.\n\n- **React.js**: A JavaScript library for building user interfaces, which is commonly used for single-page applications (SPAs) like Quora.\n\n- **TypeScript**: Possibly used in conjunction with JavaScript to add static typing, which helps in catching errors early and improving code quality.\n\n- **C++**: Used for performance-critical components. For example, Quora uses C++ for its real-time feed ranking system.\n\n- **Go (Golang)**: Used for certain microservices and infrastructure-related tasks. Go is known for its performance and simplicity, making it a good choice for scalable systems.\n\n- **SQL**: For database management and querying. Quora uses relational databases to store and manage data, and SQL is the standard language for interacting with these databases.\n\n- **HTML/CSS**: Essential for structuring and styling web pages.\n\nIn addition to these languages, Quora leverages various frameworks, libraries, and tools to enhance development efficiency and system performance. The exact tech stack can evolve over time as the platform grows and new technologies emerge.",
